pddl.prompt:
Here is the natural language description of the floor-tile domain:
{environment->context_inputs->NL_DOMAIN}

Here is the incomplete PDDL domain template:
{environment->context_inputs->PDDL_DOMAIN_TEMPLATE}

Complete the PDDL domain definition, filling in the predicates section, and the precondition, effect, and cost fields for all seven actions (change-color, paint-up, paint-down, up, down, right, left). 
Enclose the final PDDL domain between <domain></domain> tags.

Here is the natural language description of the problem:
{environment->context_inputs->NL_PROBLEM}

Here is the PDDL problem template:
{environment->context_inputs->PDDL_PROBLEM_TEMPLATE}

Review the template. If it is accurate and complete based on the NL description, output it exactly. If corrections are needed (e.g., missing predicates mentioned in the NL but not initialized), correct it. Since this problem involves two robots, ensure all objects and initial states are correctly defined.
Enclose the final PDDL problem between <problem></problem> tags.

You have received the complete PDDL domain and the verified PDDL problem file for the floor-tile multi-robot planning task. 

Goal: {agents->orchestrator->goal}

Use the following inputs:

PDDL Domain:
{pddl_domain_complete}

PDDL Problem:
{pddl_problem_complete}

Ensure that the combined PDDL definition is valid and ready for execution by a PDDL solver.
Enclose the final PDDL domain between <domain></domain> tags, and the final PDDL problem between <problem></problem> tags.
